%%capture

dc = results_df['City'] == 'Washington' # DC
md = results_df['City'] == 'Baltimore' # Baltimore
va = results_df['State'] == 'VA' # Virginia
alex = results_df['City'] == 'Alexandria' # Alexandira
rich = results_df['City'] == 'Richmond' # Richmond

dmv_df = results_df[dc | md | (va & (alex | rich))]

def split_geo(row):
    xy = row['Geolocation'].replace('(','').replace(')','').split(',')
    x = xy[0]; y = xy[1]
    dmv_df.loc[row.name, 'Latitude'] = float(x)
    dmv_df.loc[row.name, 'Longitude'] = float(y)

dmv_df.apply(split_geo, axis=1)
dmv_df.drop('Geolocation', axis=1, inplace=True)

# Create a series showing what questions correlate the most with shitty mental health
r = pd.DataFrame(columns=questions)

for q in questions:
    r.loc[0,q] = float(dmv_df['Mental Health'].corr(dmv_df[q]))

r = r.transpose()
r.columns = ['r']
r.sort_values('r', ascending=False)
